vulnerability.name: USN-4216-2
vulnerability.description: USN-4216-1 fixed vulnerabilities in Firefox. This update provides the corresponding update for Ubuntu 16.04 LTS.  Original advisory details:   Multiple security issues were discovered in Firefox. If a user were  tricked in to opening a specially crafted website, an attacker could  potentially exploit these to cause a denial of service, obtain sensitive  information, or execute arbitrary code.

statements.status_notes: Firefox could be made to crash or run programs as your login if it opened a malicious website.
